# CODEOWNERS — defense-in-depth for sensitive plumbing.
#
# The primary security boundary for this repo is `pull_request` (no secrets)
# + branch protection on `main` (PR + maintainer approval required to merge).
# That alone closes the direct exfiltration path that motivated the CI rework.
#
# This file is the second layer: any change to the files listed below
# requires explicit maintainer review on the PR — even from another
# maintainer — before merge is permitted. The rationale is that mistakes
# (or hostile contributions) in these files are the kind of thing that
# could subvert the trust boundary itself.
#
# See specs/ci-rework.md §10.
#
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ACTION REQUIRED before merge:
#   The team handle below (`@brooklyn-data/dbt-artifacts-maintainers`) is a
#   placeholder. Replace with the actual team slug (or list of individual
#   usernames) responsible for maintaining this repo. Verify with the
#   GitHub org admin if unsure.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CI / build plumbing — changes here can subvert the security model.
